{"title_page": "Ahmed Galal (politician)", "text_new": "{{distinguish|text=[[Ahmed Galal]]''}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=July 2013}}\n{{Infobox officeholder\n| name = Ahmed Galal\n| image   = \n| imagesize = \n| caption       = \n| office = [[Minister of Finance (Egypt)|Minister of Finance]]\n| primeminister = [[Hazem Al Beblawi]]\n| predecessor = [[Fayyad Abdel Moneim]]\n| successor = [[Hani Qadri Demian]]\n| term_start = 16 July 2013\n| term_end = 1 March 2014\n| office2 = \n| primeminister2= \n| predecessor2 = \n| successor2 = \n| term_start2 = \n| term_end2 = \n| birth_date = \n| birth_place =\n| death_date = \n| death_place      = \n| restingplace     = \n| party =[[Independent (politician)|Independent]]\n| residence = \n| alma_mater =[[Cairo University]]<br/> [[the American University in Cairo|American University in Cairo]]<br/>[[Boston University]]\n| profession    = Economist\n| spouse = \n| nationality =[[Egyptians|Egyptian]]\n| religion= \n| children = \n| website = \n| footnotes = \n}}\n\n'''Ahmed Galal''' is an Egyptian economist and politician, who was appointed [[Minister of Finance (Egypt)|minister of finance]] in the [[interim government]] headed by [[Hazem Al Beblawi]] on 16 July 2013.<ref name=ao16july>{{cite news|title=Egypt's interim president swears in first government|url=http://english.ahram.org.eg/NewsContent/1/64/76619/Egypt/Politics-/BREAKING-Egypts-interim-president-is-swearing-in-f.aspx|accessdate=18 July 2013|work=Ahram Online|date=16 July 2013}}</ref>\n\n==Early life and education==\nGalal received a bachelor's degree in business administration from [[Cairo University]] in 1973.<ref name=erpman>{{cite web|title=ERP Managing Director |url=http://www.erf.org.eg/cms.php?id=erf_affiliates_research_fellows_details&affiliates_id=261 |work=Economic Research Forum |accessdate=17 July 2013 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150210151420/http://www.erf.org.eg/cms.php?id=erf_affiliates_research_fellows_details&affiliates_id=261 |archivedate=10 February 2015 }}</ref>  Next he obtained a master's degree in economics from [[the American University in Cairo]] in 1984.<ref name=erpman/> He also holds a PhD in economics, which he received from [[Boston University]] in 1986.<ref name=erpman/>\n\n==Career==\nGalal began his career at [[World Bank]] in 1984 and worked there for eighteen years.<ref name=erpman/> He was the executive director and director of research of the Egyptian Center for Economic Studies (ECES) for two terms (1996-1997 and 2000-2006).<ref name=erpman/> In 2007 he was appointed member of the international board of governors of [[International Development Research Center|the International Development Research Center (IDRC)]] in [[Canada]].<ref name=erpman/> He is the president of Forum Eurom\u00e9diterran\u00e9en des Instituts de Sciences \u00c9conomiques (FEMISE) in [[France]], and the founding co-chairman of the Board of the MENA Health Policy Forum in [[Jordan]].<ref name=erpman/>\n\nHe has been the managing director of the Economic Research Forum (ERF), a Cairo-based non-governmental research institution on [[the Middle East]], since 2007.<ref name=ahon15july>{{cite news|title=Economist Ahmed Galal to be Egypt's new finance minister|url=http://english.ahram.org.eg/NewsContent/3/12/76536/Business/Economy/Economist-Ahmed-Galal-to-be-Egypts-new-finance-min.aspx|accessdate=17 July 2013|work=Ahram Online|date=15 July 2013}}</ref> He involved in the economic development initiative started by former prime minister [[Hisham Qandil]] in December 2012.<ref name=ahon15july/> Galal, an independent politician, was appointed finance minister on 16 July 2013 to the interim government led by Prime Minister Hazem Al Beblawi.<ref name=fam17jul>{{cite news|title=Egyptian Premier Returns to Cage He Escaped Facing More Violence|url=https://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-07-16/egyptian-premier-returns-to-cage-he-escaped-facing-more-violence.html|accessdate=17 July 2013|work=Bloomberg|date=17 July 2013|author=Alaa Shahine|author2=Mariam Fam}}</ref><ref name=abi16jul>{{cite news|last=Hauslohner|first=Abigail|title=Interim Egyptian cabinet sworn in|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/world/middle_east/deadly-clashes-erupt-in-cairo-after-us-diplomats-visit/2013/07/16/8fef7e1c-edff-11e2-9008-61e94a7ea20d_story.html|accessdate=16 July 2013|newspaper=The Washington Post|date=16 July 2013|location=Cairo}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{Beblawi Cabinet|state=collapsed}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Galal, Ahmed}}\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Cairo University alumni]]\n[[Category:Boston University alumni]]\n[[Category:American University in Cairo alumni]]\n[[Category:Egyptian economists]]\n[[Category:Beblawi Cabinet]]\n[[Category:Finance Ministers of Egypt]]\n[[Category:Year of birth missing (living people)]]\n", "text_old": "{{distinguish|text=[[Ahmed Galal]]''}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=July 2013}}\n{{Infobox Minister\n| name = Ahmed Galal\n| image   = \n| imagesize = \n| caption       = \n| office = [[Minister of Finance (Egypt)|Minister of Finance]]\n| primeminister = [[Hazem Al Beblawi]]\n| predecessor = [[Fayyad Abdel Moneim]]\n| successor = [[Hani Qadri Demian]]\n| term_start = 16 July 2013\n| term_end = 1 March 2014\n| office2 = \n| primeminister2= \n| predecessor2 = \n| successor2 = \n| term_start2 = \n| term_end2 = \n| birth_date = \n| birth_place =\n| death_date = \n| death_place      = \n| restingplace     = \n| party =[[Independent (politician)|Independent]]\n| residence = \n| alma_mater =[[Cairo University]]<br/> [[the American University in Cairo|American University in Cairo]]<br/>[[Boston University]]\n| profession    = Economist\n| spouse = \n| nationality =[[Egyptians|Egyptian]]\n| religion= \n| children = \n| website = \n| footnotes = \n}}\n\n'''Ahmed Galal''' is an Egyptian economist and politician, who was appointed [[Minister of Finance (Egypt)|minister of finance]] in the [[interim government]] headed by [[Hazem Al Beblawi]] on 16 July 2013.<ref name=ao16july>{{cite news|title=Egypt's interim president swears in first government|url=http://english.ahram.org.eg/NewsContent/1/64/76619/Egypt/Politics-/BREAKING-Egypts-interim-president-is-swearing-in-f.aspx|accessdate=18 July 2013|work=Ahram Online|date=16 July 2013}}</ref>\n\n==Early life and education==\nGalal received a bachelor's degree in business administration from [[Cairo University]] in 1973.<ref name=erpman>{{cite web|title=ERP Managing Director |url=http://www.erf.org.eg/cms.php?id=erf_affiliates_research_fellows_details&affiliates_id=261 |work=Economic Research Forum |accessdate=17 July 2013 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150210151420/http://www.erf.org.eg/cms.php?id=erf_affiliates_research_fellows_details&affiliates_id=261 |archivedate=10 February 2015 }}</ref>  Next he obtained a master's degree in economics from [[the American University in Cairo]] in 1984.<ref name=erpman/> He also holds a PhD in economics, which he received from [[Boston University]] in 1986.<ref name=erpman/>\n\n==Career==\nGalal began his career at [[World Bank]] in 1984 and worked there for eighteen years.<ref name=erpman/> He was the executive director and director of research of the Egyptian Center for Economic Studies (ECES) for two terms (1996-1997 and 2000-2006).<ref name=erpman/> In 2007 he was appointed member of the international board of governors of [[International Development Research Center|the International Development Research Center (IDRC)]] in [[Canada]].<ref name=erpman/> He is the president of Forum Eurom\u00e9diterran\u00e9en des Instituts de Sciences \u00c9conomiques (FEMISE) in [[France]], and the founding co-chairman of the Board of the MENA Health Policy Forum in [[Jordan]].<ref name=erpman/>\n\nHe has been the managing director of the Economic Research Forum (ERF), a Cairo-based non-governmental research institution on [[the Middle East]], since 2007.<ref name=ahon15july>{{cite news|title=Economist Ahmed Galal to be Egypt's new finance minister|url=http://english.ahram.org.eg/NewsContent/3/12/76536/Business/Economy/Economist-Ahmed-Galal-to-be-Egypts-new-finance-min.aspx|accessdate=17 July 2013|work=Ahram Online|date=15 July 2013}}</ref> He involved in the economic development initiative started by former prime minister [[Hisham Qandil]] in December 2012.<ref name=ahon15july/> Galal, an independent politician, was appointed finance minister on 16 July 2013 to the interim government led by Prime Minister Hazem Al Beblawi.<ref name=fam17jul>{{cite news|title=Egyptian Premier Returns to Cage He Escaped Facing More Violence|url=https://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-07-16/egyptian-premier-returns-to-cage-he-escaped-facing-more-violence.html|accessdate=17 July 2013|work=Bloomberg|date=17 July 2013|author=Alaa Shahine|author2=Mariam Fam}}</ref><ref name=abi16jul>{{cite news|last=Hauslohner|first=Abigail|title=Interim Egyptian cabinet sworn in|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/world/middle_east/deadly-clashes-erupt-in-cairo-after-us-diplomats-visit/2013/07/16/8fef7e1c-edff-11e2-9008-61e94a7ea20d_story.html|accessdate=16 July 2013|newspaper=The Washington Post|date=16 July 2013|location=Cairo}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{Beblawi Cabinet|state=collapsed}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Galal, Ahmed}}\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Cairo University alumni]]\n[[Category:Boston University alumni]]\n[[Category:American University in Cairo alumni]]\n[[Category:Egyptian economists]]\n[[Category:Beblawi Cabinet]]\n[[Category:Finance Ministers of Egypt]]\n[[Category:Year of birth missing (living people)]]\n", "name_user": "Ser Amantio di Nicolao", "label": "safe", "comment": "add authority control", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ahmed_Galal_(politician)"}
